The paper discusses lessons learned from pilot projects in the DEPLOY project, which aimed to develop methods and tools for the deployment of dependable systems. The focus is on the use of formal methods, specifically the Event-B formalism, in the development process. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the limitations of using a single formalism and the need to use appropriate formalisms and tools for different phases of the development process, which suggests relevance to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also touches on the use of formal methods in ensuring dependability, which could relate to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
